## BT Secretary app
Scaffolding mobile Phase 1 (Capacitor + iOS + Android).

### Status (Phase 1.0)

- App Capacitor scaffolded
- App ID: `ca.comptaria.btsecretary`
- WebDir: `../public` (wrapper HTML of the Comptaria marketing site, will be replaced by the BT Secretary app shell at M1.1)
- Platforms: android/ ios/

### Run locally

```bash
cd /var/www/comptaria.ca/mobile
npm install
# Build the web bundle first (see ../package.json "build" script) — for now, npx cap sync copies ../public
npx cap sync android    # copies web assets and updates plugins
npx cap sync ios
npx cap open android    # opens Android Studio
npx cap open ios        # opens Xcode (on macOS)
```

### Architecture (Phase 1 spec)

- App container: Capacitor (iOS + Android)
- Web shell: HTML+JS from `../public` (will be replaced by `app.btsecretary.html`)
- Native plugins: `@capacitor/camera, filesystem, network, preferences, share` (already installed)
- Backend MCP (separate): `mcp-comtaria` (DB) + `mcp-csv` v0.2 (brand + structured + visual) + `mcp-acomba` (wrapper)
- Auth: OIDC cabinet-level, MFA
- Offline mode: queue persistante (IndexedDB + Service Worker)

### Roadmap

See `docs/strategy/10-bt-secretary-app-v0.1-roadmap.md` in the
`comptaria.ca` repository for the full Partie 1 plan.

This directory is part of the same monorepo (`comptaria.ca`). It will be
contributed to via PRs on `feat/app-bt-secretary-v0` once the web shell
exists.
